summary: Heyyy què fort trobar un altre fan català d’Andi Mack😂 Have you ever watched the show in Spanish? If so, what do you think about...
question: Heyyy què fort trobar un altre fan català d’Andi Mack😂 Have you ever watched the show in Spanish? If so, what do you think about TJ’s nickname for Cyrus being translated to “Columpios”?
answer:
ASSDFFGHHJJ ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜 I tant! Jo creia que, amb sort, hi trobaria un parell de castellans i ja!

I haven’t! I found out about the show because it was trending on here due to the S3 promo. But here’s an unnecessarily long review anyways.

If columpios (that’s Spanish for swings, for those who didn’t know) is used where TJ says underdog, I totally get it. I mean, I’ve tried searching on the internet what underdog means, and I still don’t think I totally get it; there’s probably no direct translation for that word.

And Columpios is a really nice nickname!! It references a really important symbol for their relationship and, at least in Spanish, has this cute, childish energy that you would expect for a first crush. Aside from that, there’s also these two scenarios based on my own experience that are worth mentioning (not really, but idc):

  • There’s my family (especially my uncles that live in Chile), who practically forget about real names and only use nicknames (my grandma was called Vieja Xexa asdfgh and they tried to call me Rorro) and Columpios would fit just fine in that context.
  • I had a phase where I would give everyone nicknames. I would use them with one specific person, and that person would also have one for me, as they always referenced internal jokes—I ended up having like 10 different nicknames. I think this is more along the lines of Columpios.

Now, I don’t know if TJ has called muffin in canon (apart from “Chocolate chocolate chip muffin” from swings scene 1.0) or it’s in my head because of fanfiction, but… If Columpios is used where TJ calls Cyrus muffin, then I would be furious!! Someone could argue that Spaniard don’t know what Muffin means, but THEY DO. Muffin >>> Columpios

summary: Confession
title: Confession
body:
I’m a person who never really uses watermarks on my art. Why? Simple, because in the end, unless you make money (which would never happen) off of something I created, then you guys can use it as you please. I don’t make it to boost my followers, or even for people to know who I am. I appreciate credit, and know why other people hate their things being used without them getting credit, but it’s not nessasary for me.

I don’t make them just for me after all, or even just Red, or Andi Mack, or whoever requested them. I’ll dedicate to people, and give credit to whoever’s idea it was, and tag people in it that I want to see it, but the true reciever is the fandom as a whole.

I make edits and moodboards because I enjoy doing it, and because I want to make even just one person smile. Maybe not everyone will enjoy all of my works, and thats okay, as long as long person enjoys it, my goal is complete. In fact that’s all I ever want to do in this fandom. Make people smile.

If someones having a bad day, I want to be able to help. If someone is just bored, I want to give them something to cure that boredom. I don’t write that often, but when I do, it’s for the smiles. Maybe I can’t see them physically, but the likes or reblogs are proof enough to me. That being said however, all I want is one like or reblog to feel acomplished. The more the better of course, because that means more smiles. 

Back to the watermarks thing though, to me, if someone steals my content then I’m flattered. That means they enjoyed it enough to want to. I know this a bad way of thinking, and to avoid arguments, I would never steal anything from anyone, but I can’t bring myself to really care that someone stole something from me. Hey, more smiles are being reached that way.

In the end, I don’t care who the smiles were created by. I just like to know that you guys are happier than you were a few seconds ago.
